						<summary>

						<p>On a rock in a field to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1558 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1480, Kāḷayukti, Śrāvaṇa ba. 1,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1558 A.D., July 31.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph seems to record the gift of some <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> at Sōmpalle, under the orders of the king and the direction of [Rāma]rājayya. Mentions Penugoṇda-sima.</p>						

						</summary>
